cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks and proposes adversarial attacks on a specific type of neural network, the Differentiable Neural Computer (DNC), which is commonly used in natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the DNC is a type of neural network, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses the security aspect of neural networks, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible sub-category.
